{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:sirach.16",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 16 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:1",
      "text": "Desire not a multitude of unprofitable children, neither delight in ungodly sons.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:2",
      "text": "Though they multiply, rejoice not in them, except the fear of the Lord be with them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:3",
      "text": "Trust not thou in their life, neither respect their multitude: for one that is just is better than a thousand; and better it is to die without children, than to have them that are ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:4",
      "text": "For by one that hath understanding shall the city be replenished: but the kindred of the wicked shall speedily become desolate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:5",
      "text": "Many such things have I seen with mine eyes, and mine ear hath heard greater things than these.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:6",
      "text": "In the congregation of the ungodly shall a fire be kindled; and in a rebellious nation wrath is set on fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:7",
      "text": "He was not pacified toward the old giants, who fell away in the strength of their foolishness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:8",
      "text": "Neither spared he the place where Lot sojourned, but abhorred them for their pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:9",
      "text": "He pitied not the people of perdition, who were taken away in their sins:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:10",
      "text": "nor the six hundred thousand footmen, who were gathered together in the hardness of their hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:11",
      "text": "And if there be one stiffnecked among the people, it is marvel if he escape unpunished: for mercy and wrath are with him; he is mighty to forgive and to pour out displeasure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:12",
      "text": "As his mercy is great, so is his correction also: he judgeth a man according to his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:13",
      "text": "The sinner shall not escape with his spoils: and the patience of the godly shall not be frustrate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:14",
      "text": "Make way for every work of mercy: for every man shall find according to his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:17",
      "text": "Say not thou, I will hide myself from the Lord: shall any remember me from above? I shall not be remembered among so many people: for what is my soul among such an infinite number of creatures?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:18",
      "text": "Behold, the heaven, and the heaven of heavens, the deep, and the earth, and all that therein is, shall be moved when he shall visit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:19",
      "text": "The mountains also and foundations of the earth shall be shaken with trembling, when he looketh upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:20",
      "text": "No heart can think upon these things worthily: and who is able to conceive his ways?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:21",
      "text": "It is a tempest which no man can see: for the most part of his works are hid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:22",
      "text": "Who can declare the works of his justice? or who can endure them? for his covenant is afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:23",
      "text": "He that wanteth understanding will think upon vain things: and a foolish man erring imagineth follies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:24",
      "text": "My son, hearken unto me, and learn knowledge, and mark my words with thy heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:25",
      "text": "I will shew forth doctrine in weight, and declare his knowledge exactly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:26",
      "text": "The works of the Lord are done in judgment from the beginning: and from the time he made them he disposed the parts thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:27",
      "text": "He garnished his works for ever, and the chief of them unto all generations: they neither labour, nor are weary, nor cease from their works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:28",
      "text": "None of them hindereth another, and they shall never disobey his word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:29",
      "text": "After this the Lord looked upon the earth, and filled it with his blessings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:sirach.16.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:30",
      "text": "With all manner of living things hath he covered the face thereof; and they shall return into it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
